notes_display: In Historical Sketches of the Paper Currency of the American Colonies by Henry Phillips, Jr. (1865). Given to Dr. Jesse C. Green in 1890. Leaf 56CF.
issue_obverse_legend_s: FORTY SHILLINGS. | THIS Indented BILL shall pass current for Forty Shillings within the Government of the Counties of New Castle, Kent, and Sussex, on Delaware, according to an Act of Assembly of the said Government, made in the 33d Year of the Reign of our Sovereign Lord King George II. Dated May 31, 1760. Two Pounds.
issue_reverse_legend_s: TWO POUNDS. | To Counterfeit is DEATH. | Printed by B. FRANKLIN, and D. HALL. 1760.
